# Teknovo Testing Rule

## DO

- Define **verification steps** for every feature before marking complete
- Run **build** (`npm run build` / project equivalent) â€” must pass before completion
- Run **tests** (`npm test`, Vitest, Playwright E2E per project) with evidence
- Apply **TDD** for business logic: `.cursor/skills/superpowers/test-driven-development/`
- Target **70%+ coverage** baseline; service unit tests for all business rules
- Verify **five page states** in UI (Loading, Empty, Error, Success, Permission)
- Run `tsc --noEmit` and linters before ship claim
- Load `.cursor/skills/superpowers/verification-before-completion/` before declaring done
- Use `gstack-qa` and `gstack-browser-testing` for functional and E2E validation

## DON'T

- Declare "done" or ship without build + test evidence
- Skip integration tests for repository/API changes when applicable
- Merge with failing CI or unresolved test failures
- Rely on manual-only verification for repeatable business logic

## Per-Feature Verification Checklist

- [ ] Unit tests for service-layer business rules
- [ ] Integration/API tests where endpoints or repos change
- [ ] RBAC matrix updated and tested (allowed + denied paths)
- [ ] UI states verified (including Permission denied view)
- [ ] Build passes locally
- [ ] Self-critique complete (`.cursor/gates/quality/self-critique.md`)

